                            <comment id="13196354" author="mikhail" created="Mon, 30 Jan 2012 19:36:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another issue that Kannan mentioned as part of a code review for the 89-fb port of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4422&quot; title=&quot;Move block cache parameters and references into single CacheConf class&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4422&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4422&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.facebook.net/D1341&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://reviews.facebook.net/D1341&lt;/a&gt;). This seems like an appropriate place to address it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the readBlockBuffer method in HFileReaderV1 we have &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;HFileReaderV1.java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
        HFileBlock cachedBlock =
          (HFileBlock) cacheConf.getBlockCache().getBlock(cacheKey,
              cacheConf.shouldCacheDataOnRead());
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but later in the method the condition used for actually caching the block is different:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;HFileReaderV1.java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Cache the block
&lt;/span&gt;      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (cacheBlock &amp;amp;&amp;amp; cacheConf.shouldCacheBlockOnRead(
          hfileBlock.getBlockType().getCategory())) {
        cacheConf.getBlockCache().cacheBlock(cacheKey, hfileBlock,
            cacheConf.isInMemory());
      }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to make these &quot;cache block&quot; flags two consistent across these two code spots as we unify getMetaBlock and readBlock&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Buffer&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, and double-check this across HFileReaderV&lt;/p&gt;
{1,2}
&lt;p&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
